item.title: Festuca muelleri
item.dc:creator: russell
item.description: Tall, wide, thick, robust grass. One plant on the dirt roadside heading down from the Horn.

item.title: Acacia alpina
item.dc:creator: russell
item.description: Common along the short dirt road leading to The Horn.

item.title: Tasmannia xerophila subsp. xerophila
item.dc:creator: russell
item.description: One flower visible with 2 petals. Growing in rocks in open herb-field. Altitude ~1470m.

item.title: Hovea montana
item.dc:creator: russell
item.description: Nearly all plants had finished flowering.

item.title: Celmisia pugioniformis
item.dc:creator: russell
item.description: Slender leaves. Seemed to be finishing flowering (flowers scruffy looking) whereas the broad-leaved C. tomentella growing with it hadn't started flowering yet.

item.title: Grevillea alpivaga
item.dc:creator: russell
item.description: To 1m tall and spreading. Midrib on underside of leaf is visible which suggests it is G. alpivaga, not G. australis. Flowering with Kunzea parvifolia.

item.title: Graphium macleayanus moggana, Westringia senifolia
item.dc:creator: russell
item.description: Host plant for Swallowtail at this location would probably be that described in observation 7933 (Tasmannia xerophila subsp. xerophila).
